The run command provides the ability to create, delete, list,
abort, execute, export, and publish runs.  The options
available for each of these actions are listed below.
The /list command allows enumerating suites in the specified plan, and
retrieving the suite name and id.
The /clone /suiteid /destinationsuiteid command starts a clone operation in TFS
to clone all test cases from a suite to a different destination suite. The destination
suite has to be in a different plan. All contained suites and test cases are cloned.
Optionally, a test case field and its value can be specified as an override to
distinguish cloned test cases from the original. The command returns an operation id
that can be used to track status and completion of the clone operation.
The /clone /status command allows tracking status and completion of a
clone operation based on its id.

ignored tests are excluded. Use /include option if you also want them in the TestSuite.
